    "content": "**KEEP \"impels.\"** The Chinese is doing different things in the two locations. 想要 (want to) is volitional — the subject retains agency. 推动 (push/drive) is causal — the feeling acts on the subject. These are epistemologically distinct: one describes a motivated agent, the other describes a mechanism. \"Moves\" and \"impels\" correctly track that distinction. Harmonizing would flatten it."
